(19, 'Managed Infrastructure Services', 'Our Managed Infrastructure Services offer you comprehensive management and monitoring of your on-premises, cloud, and IT infrastructure so you can improve operational agility, minimize risk and optimize cloud and technology infrastructure investments.\r\n\r\nConcentrate on achieving organizational goals and make sure your IT infrastructure is resilient and running at its best. Comprehensive on-premises, cloud, and IT infrastructure management and proactive monitoring are provided by our Managed Infrastructure Services. Your IT infrastructure\'s day-to-day operations will be handled by our highly trained, vendor-accredited experts, processes, and tools.', '<p><strong>Key outcomes</strong></p><p><strong>Security</strong></p><p>Our secure-by-design services portfolio ensures the administration and compliance of our solutions whether on-premises or in the cloud.</p><p><strong>Reliability</strong></p><p>Better control of internal and external assets, and optimized IT expenditure.</p><p><strong>Intelligent</strong></p><p>Unpack the value of data for better customer experience and processes using intelligent managed cloud infrastructure services.</p><p><strong>Automation</strong></p><p>Automate infrastructure to drive digital transformation for your connected enterprise.</p><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Why Inbox Infotech?&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Management</strong></p><p>End-to-end management hosted, on-premises, and in the cloud.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Ecosystem</strong></p><p>Partnerships with major vendors in the IT industry</p><p><strong>Delivery</strong></p><p>ITIL-compliant global integrated service delivery model</p><p><strong>Focus&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Concentrate on client satisfaction and ongoing improvement</p><p><br>&nbsp;</p><h4><strong>IT Infrastructure Components We Cover</strong></h4><p>Continuous monitoring, support, and optimization of your IT infrastructure or its components are our responsibility:</p><ul><li>Servers (Linux, Windows).</li><li>Cloud environments (AWS, Azure, GCP).</li><li>Data storage &amp; databases (cloud-based &amp; on-premises).</li><li>Network &amp; security (VPN, LAN, Firewall, Antivirus, IDS/IPS, IAM, SIEM).</li><li>Customer-facing software.</li><li>Enterprise solutions (Email, ERP, CRM, Intranet.)</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>Scope of IT Infrastructure Managed Services by Inbox</strong></h3><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>#1. IT infrastructure consulting &amp; monitoring</strong></p><p>• Observing and streamlining asset utilization.</p><p>• Tuning infrastructure components and analyzing performance</p><p>• Setting up and arranging checking devices.</p><p>• Streamlining the ticketing process.</p><p>• Security audit and monitoring of the infrastructure.</p><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong># 2. IT help desk and troubleshooting</strong></p><p>• Dealing with a wide range of complex and serious incidents.</p><p>• Locating the underlying causes of incidents.</p><p>• Looking at how an incident might affect business and suggesting ways to avoid it</p><p>• Immediate patching</p><p>• Recovery from disasters.</p><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>#3. IT infrastructure evolution</strong></p><p>Designing, putting into action, distributing, and configuring brand-new pieces of infrastructure.</p><p>Moving infrastructure or a portion of it to the cloud, such as Azure or AWS, for example.</p><p>Support for existing components\' integration, upkeep, and technical and functional functions.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>How Inbox Infotech Delivers IT Infrastructure Managed Services</strong></h3><h4><strong>Infrastructure analysis</strong></h4><p><strong>Timeline:</strong> ~2-4 weeks.</p><p>We look at your current IT infrastructure design, talk to your business and technical stakeholders, or we talk to third-party vendors, to find out more about how your IT infrastructure components are set up and what assets are available.</p><h4><strong>Responsibility transfer</strong></h4><p><strong>Timeline:</strong> ~2-4 weeks.</p><p>We undertake the entire responsibility of your IT infrastructure.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><strong>Service delivery</strong></h4><p><strong>Continuous service</strong></p><p>We provide either a complete set of IT infrastructure-managed services or maintenance of specific IT environment components, depending on the service option selected.</p><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><h4><strong>Evolution</strong></h4><p><strong>Timeline:&nbsp;</strong>New functionality can be delivered in one day to two weeks, and urgent changes can be implemented within eight working hours.</p><p>We make adjustments to your IT infrastructure to make it more flexible and reliable.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1672303666.webp', 'managed-infrastructure-services', NULL, 'fas fa-server', NULL, 'managed-infrastructure-services', NULL, NULL, 'Ankur', 'Ankur', '0', NULL, '2022-12-22 14:59:27', '2022-12-29 14:17:46'),
(20, 'Managed Application Services', 'Managed application services are a method to keep your applications highly handy and relevant to growing business needs. For a long, Inbox Infotech has been offering scalable, reliable, and powerful application support, evolution & optimization.', '<h4><strong>Why Inbox Infotech?</strong></h4><ul><li>Nine Gold Microsoft competencies, including Content Competencies, Collaboration, and Application Development and Integration.</li><li>Strategic alliances with a variety of tech leaders, including Amazon, IBM, Oracle, Magento, Pimcore, Salesforce, &amp; ServiceNow.</li><li>A help desk with representatives fluent in English, German, Spanish, French, Polish, Czech, Turkish, and other languages.</li><li>Knowledge of IT environments that are both complex and diverse.</li><li>Time-tested methods for resolving issues.</li><li>Capacity to bring innovation and excellence to each project, as demonstrated by inclusion in the prestigious Global Outsourcing 100 list.</li><li>Focus on specific goals and requirements for the business.</li></ul><h4><strong>Applications We Focus On</strong></h4><p>Inbox Infotech has a record of successful management and upgrade of a number of enterprise-level solutions.</p><h4><br><strong>Industry expertise:</strong></h4><ul><li>Manufacturing</li><li>Banking</li><li>Retail &amp; eCommerce</li><li>Professional services</li><li>Healthcare</li><li>Telecommunications, etc.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><strong>Business process expertise:</strong></h4><ul><li>Supply chain &amp; procurement management</li><li>Sales management</li><li>Financial management</li><li>Customer service management</li><li>Marketing campaigns management, &amp; more.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>Explore Inbox Infotech Managed Application Services</strong></h3><p>The application monitoring, problem-solving, system availability, reliability management, continuous app refinement, and help desk provision offered by Inbox Infotech comprise a comprehensive portfolio of services. The business\'s specific requirements can be met by combining and contrasting any number of services.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>Application monitoring and performance management</strong></h3><p>Holding responsibility regarding application execution of the executives, Inbox Infotech group executes an extensive variety of observing exercises to watch out for every single basic measurement, for example, reaction time, exchange fruition, message line surpasses, and identify and determine expected risks before they create any serious cycle interruption or harm UX.</p><p>Inbox Infotech addresses application misbehaviors, component unavailability, slow request handling, excessive memory consumption, data inaccuracy, inconsistency, and other issues to keep the application functioning properly.</p><p>Enhancement of applications the team at Inbox Infotech makes certain minor and major application modifications, updates, and rollouts of new versions are managed in an orderly and timely manner.</p><p>Inbox Infotech can help with application optimization to keep the apps relevant to the changing business context, increase their ROI, and reduce their total cost of ownership. We conduct a business process review to identify existing pain points and modify applications (e.g., automate, migrate to new technologies and platforms, restructure or modularize solutions) to speed up ineffective flows and make maintenance simpler.</p><p>Services for change management and training in order to successfully manage app modifications, our team pays adequate attention to each fundamental step of the change process. We look at the reasons behind a change, make sure that all testing is covered, figure out the risks, make a safe release plan, and do the post-change review.</p><p>Inbox Infotech also makes sure that new app components and upgraded or extended versions of the ones you already have are easily integrated into your IT environment. Customized training—in the form of step-by-step guides, on-site workshops, webinars, etc.—accomplishes the delivery. for various departments and users so that they can get the most out of the updates.</p><p>Application security professionals at Inbox Infotech carry out activities like monitoring and testing to avoid data breaches caused by application flaws.</p><p>Capabilities of the Help Desk Our managed application services can also be strengthened with help desk support. With prompt responses and a knowledge base that is constantly updated, a multilingual help desk (24*7) makes it easier for app users to get help. In addition, it improves the work of higher-level support teams by correctly prioritizing tasks and by providing comprehensive reports on tickets that have been resolved.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><strong>How We Get Started?</strong></h4><p>The established plan for the transition assists us in responsibility without a hitch. We always begin our cooperation by following four crucial steps:</p><h4><strong>Software quality assessment</strong></h4><p>Every project begins with a comprehensive quality assessment of the applications we will serve—whether carried out by us, the client or a third-party vendor. As a result, we estimate the applications\' actual state, plan a service scope that is more efficient and relevant to their needs, and selects the best KPIs to track application operations improvements.</p><h4><strong>Knowledge Transfer</strong></h4><p>We take the time to thoroughly comprehend your application. The Inbox Infotech team looks into the technical and functional app specifications and code documentation that is already in place extracts business rules directly from the software code and communicates with your employees.</p><h4><strong>Service planning and SLA preparation</strong></h4><p>We go over the service scope in detail, tailoring it to your requirements. Together, we assign responsibilities, establish performance benchmarks, select appropriate communication tools, define the reporting schedule, and select the data security level in order to keep the process clear and avoid any disruptions or blind spots.</p><h4><strong>Responsibility transfer</strong></h4><p>We begin carrying out the planned services and assume the agreed-upon scope of responsibility.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1672304708.webp', 'managed-application-services', NULL, 'fas fa-server', NULL, 'managed-application-services', NULL, NULL, 'Ankur', 'Ankur', '0', NULL, '2022-12-22 15:56:20', '2022-12-29 14:35:08'),
(21, 'Managed Cloud Services', 'Manage, Optimize and Enhance Cloud Efficiency\r\nCloud Service Providers (CSPs) are getting a boost from industry-wide cloud adoption.\r\nThe inability of organizations to manage all cloud-related tasks internally is the primary driver of reliance on CSPs.\r\nIn the end, this is what led to the \"Cloud Managed Services\" craze in the United States.\r\nBy delegating complete control of your cloud operations to Cloud Managed Service Providers (MSPs), \"Cloud Managed Services\" provide you with comprehensive cloud management support.', '<h2><strong>Why Cloud Managed Services?</strong></h2><p><br>Despite the growing popularity of cloud computing in the United States, efficient management is still the top priority for the majority of businesses. Organizations based in the United States select various cloud infrastructure management strategies to address this issue. Some people manage it themselves, while others hire a Cloud MSP to alleviate immediate difficulties. Still, others select a managed cloud service provider with a clear vision for managing hybrid environments and resources to handle larger tasks.</p><p><strong>Whatever the circumstance, the goal is to locate the ideal solution for efficient cloud management! A bad plan can result in:</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>The rise in operational risks</strong></h3><p>It\'s critical to choose a Cloud MSP that fits your needs. Failing to do so could halt the operation of revenue-generating models like sales and supply chains and pose serious operational risks to your cloud infrastructure-based processes.</p><h3><strong>Rise of security risks</strong></h3><p>Risks to cloud security are getting worse for applications that run on the public cloud. Because of this, having the right security plan in place is crucial to avoiding risks like these.</p><h3><strong>Less Value</strong></h3><p>Cloud migration can be costly and take longer than anticipated if the appropriate service support is not provided.</p><p>The aforementioned issues and many others that are necessary for efficient cloud infrastructure management can all be addressed by the ideal cloud-managed service provider.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>End-to-End Managed Cloud Services</strong></h3><p>Cloud Deployment Cloud Security</p><p>Cloud Security Network and Storage</p><p>Network and Storage Cloud Monitoring and Reporting</p><p>Cloud Monitoring and Reporting Backup and Disaster Recovery</p><p>Backup and Disaster Recovery Infrastructure Set Up</p><p>Infrastructure Set Up Business Continuity</p><p>Business Continuity Cloud Migration Services</p><p>Cloud Migration Services</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Cloud Deployment Cloud Security</p><p>Cloud Security Network and Storage</p><p>Network and Storage Cloud Monitoring and Reporting</p><p>Cloud Monitoring and Reporting Backup and Disaster Recovery</p><p>Backup and Disaster Recovery Infrastructure Set Up</p><p>Infrastructure Set Up Business Continuity</p><p>Business Continuity Cloud Migration Services</p><p>Cloud Migration Services</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1671707045.png', 'Managed Cloud Services', NULL, 'managed-cloud-services', NULL, 'managed-cloud-services1', NULL, NULL, 'Ankur', 'Ankur', '0', '2022-12-22 17:25:27', '2022-12-22 16:34:05', '2022-12-22 17:25:27');
